Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve,
core, and slice @long green pepper{1} into ½-inch-thick strips. Peel and thinly
slice @red onion{1} into rounds.

Toss zucchini and green pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp},
@southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{1/2%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high
heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.
Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat.
Add onion rounds and cook, undisturbed, until deeply browned and tender,
~{2-3%minutes} per side. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Use pan used for chicken here.

Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in pan used for onion over medium heat.
Add baguettes, cut sides down, and toast until golden brown, ~{1-3%minutes}.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to toast in batches, using a
> large drizzle of olive oil for each batch.

Spread cut sides of baguettes with half the spicy guacamole. Fill with as many
onion rounds and roasted veggies as you like.

Slice chicken crosswise. Add to sandwiches along with roasted veggies.

Divide sandwiches, @blue corn tortilla chips{3%oz}, any remaining onion rounds,
and any remaining roasted veggies between plates. Serve with remaining spicy
guacamole on the side for dipping.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.